The paper presents a new kernel method for analysing multivariate time series subject to missing data. The approach is based on Bayesian mixture models and uses an ensemble learning strategy, making it particularly well suited for unsupervised learning. The paper also proposes a semi-supervised kernel that takes advantage of incomplete label information. Given these characteristics, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also deals with missing data, which suggests a possible fit with cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
